HEADWORD: Hypogynous
<hw>Hy*pog"y*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>hypo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ woman, female: cf. F.
<ets>hypogyne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Inserted below the
pistil or pistils; -- said of sepals, petals, and stamens; having the
sepals, petals, and stamens inserted below the pistil; -- said of a
flower or a plant.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

